    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2005 Porsche 911 Carrera (997.1) represents a pure driver\u2019s configuration, powered by a 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a 6-speed manual transaxle with a precise, short-throw linkage. The chassis features Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) and a hydraulic steering rack for unparalleled tactile feedback. Recent preventative maintenance includes the critical IMS bearing and Rear Main Seal (RMS) updates, ensuring the M96 powerplant remains robust. The braking system utilizes four-piston aluminum monoblock calipers over vented, cross-drilled rotors, providing exceptional thermal management and firm pedal feel. This is a well-sorted example with a taut suspension and linear throttle response, ideal for the purist seeking a communicative, analog driving experience.",
      "price": 36500.0,
